// Storm's Beacon - the pilot episodes. A single-ship STORY universe on the universe_core
// mastlib (Mode: story, no admiral economy). Prof. Storm is VIRTUAL CREW: hail her on the
// Ultra-Beam (with no target selected) for each lead. She reveals the next site; you
// Engage-jump there from the Quests tab and scan the ancient ruin, then hail her again for
// the next heading. Two Storm-gated episodes here; the full campaign (reputation, XORN,
// crafting, Crazy Eddy) builds out from this spine - see STORMS_BEACON.md.

# Storm's Beacon
---
Display: Storms Beacon
---
Prof. Storm has a lead on the Beacon - an ancient signal buried in the ruins the old
giants left behind. Hail her for each heading, follow the clues, and stay a jump ahead of
whatever is hunting the same trail.

## Scenario
---
Mode: story
---

## Lifeforms

### Professor Storm (prof_storm)
---
Face: female
Roles: advisor
Scene: storm_hail
Color: #6cf
---
Expedition lead and xeno-archaeologist. A host-less advisor - hail her from anywhere on
the Ultra-Beam (no target selected) for the next lead on the Beacon.

### Crazy Eddy (crazy_eddy)
---
Face: male
Roles: advisor, eddy
Scene: eddy_hail
Color: #fa0
---
A back-channel ship-dealer working the old marches out of a ramshackle hull. Sells gear
nobody else will - some of it even works. A host-less advisor: hail him on the Ultra-Beam
(no target selected) to browse his deals. Cash up front, no refunds.

### Chief Engineer Vex (chief_vex)
---
Face: female
Roles: advisor, engineer
Scene: vex_hail
Color: #8f8
---
Your chief engineer - keeps this under-gunned little ship flying on scavenged parts and
spite. Hail her on the Ultra-Beam for a read on the ship and a piece of her mind.

### Madame Skarr (madame_skarr)
---
Face: female
Roles: advisor, skarr
Scene: skarr_hail
Color: #7c4
---
A Skaraan treasure-broker, hell-bent on selling the Beacon to the highest bidder - and not
much fussed whether it's whole or prised off your wreck. She hired the hunters on your tail.
Hail her on the Ultra-Beam to deal, or to tell her where to go.

### The Bounty Hunters (bounty_crew)
---
Face: male
Roles: bounty_hunter
Scene: bounty_hail
Color: #db4
---
Two hunters in one battered ship on Madame Skarr's contract. One does the talking; the other,
Dobbs, does the shooting and can't be bothered with the rest. The voice on your comms when the
Second Wind runs you down.

## Dialogue

### Professor Storm (storm_hail)
---
Speaker: prof_storm
When: comms
---
% Storm here, Captain. What do you need?
% Go ahead - I'm knee-deep in old star charts.
% Talk to me. The trail's still warm.

- [Any word on the Beacon?](storm_hail) ; signal storm_check
- [Just checking in](storm_smalltalk)

### Professor Storm (storm_smalltalk)
---
Speaker: prof_storm
---
% Watch yourself out there. The Beacon isn't the only thing hunting these ruins.
% Keep the ship quiet and the sensors hot. We find it by being clever, not loud.

// Crazy Eddy's Emporium. The shop is DECLARATIVE dialogue: each deal is a choice gated on
// `if credits >= N`, charged by `; costs N credits`, and wired to a MAST `//signal/eddy_buy_*`
// route (story.mast) that applies the REAL ship modifier. Some deals are honest, some are
// traps, some are a coin-flip - the route decides. The `eddy_sold` line is just his patter;
// the actual up/down result comes back as a comms message from the route.

### Crazy Eddy (eddy_hail)
---
Speaker: crazy_eddy
When: comms
---
% Eddy's the name, salvage is the game! Step right up, captain.
% You look like a soul in need of an upgrade. Lucky you - I'm having a sale.
% No refunds, no returns, no questions asked. What'll it be?

- [Show me the deals](eddy_shop)
- [Not today, Eddy](eddy_bye)

### Eddy's Deals (eddy_shop)
---
Speaker: crazy_eddy
---
% Every piece genuine salvage, pried off wrecks with my own two hands. Cash up front!

// Each buy earns `crazy_eddy generous` standing (spending freely makes you his favorite).
// At generous > 15 the "Regulars only" branch unlocks (rep gates a discounted menu) - the
// tactical AND narrative rep use. Rep is per-captain, persisted across episodes.
- [Salvaged Sensor Array - 400cr](eddy_sold) if credits >= 400 ; costs 400 credits, signal eddy_buy_sensor, earns crazy_eddy generous 3
- [Overclocked Impulse Coils - 250cr](eddy_sold) if credits >= 250 ; costs 250 credits, signal eddy_buy_coils, earns crazy_eddy generous 3
- [Reinforced Plating, a STEAL - 150cr](eddy_sold) if credits >= 150 ; costs 150 credits, signal eddy_buy_plating, earns crazy_eddy generous 3
- [Mystery Crate, feeling lucky? - 200cr](eddy_sold) if credits >= 200 ; costs 200 credits, signal eddy_buy_mystery, earns crazy_eddy generous 3
- [That big giant-tech frame - the Resonance Cradle - 500cr](eddy_cradle_sold) if credits >= 500 ; costs 500 credits, signal eddy_buy_cradle, earns crazy_eddy generous 5
- [Regulars only - the good stuff](eddy_loyal) if generous > 15
- [Never mind](eddy_hail)

### Regulars Only (eddy_loyal)
---
Speaker: crazy_eddy
---
% For my best customer? I keep the honest stuff under the counter. No gambles, just gear.
% You've been good to me, captain. So I'll be good to you. Discount, and no funny business.

- [Sensor Array, friends price - 250cr](eddy_sold) if credits >= 250 ; costs 250 credits, signal eddy_buy_sensor, earns crazy_eddy generous 2
- [Genuine Shield Emitters - 300cr](eddy_sold) if credits >= 300 ; costs 300 credits, signal eddy_buy_shield, earns crazy_eddy generous 2
- [Back](eddy_shop)

### Sold! (eddy_sold)
