% Sold! To the captain with more credits than sense.

- [More deals](eddy_shop)
- [I'm done here](eddy_bye)

### The Cradle (eddy_cradle_sold)
---
Speaker: crazy_eddy
---
% The big ugly frame? Ha! Knew it'd find a buyer eventually. Never could unload the thing -
% too heavy, too weird, hums when you look at it wrong. All yours, captain. No refunds!
% Careful hauling that home. Feels like it's WAITING for something. Gives me the creeps.

- [More deals](eddy_shop)
- [I'm done here](eddy_bye)

### Come Back Soon (eddy_bye)
---
Speaker: crazy_eddy
---
% Your loss. I'll be here, marinating in the dark.
% Fly safe. Or don't - salvage is salvage.

// Chief Engineer Vex - the ship's own voice. Flavor + tone reinforcement (under-gunned,
// run don't fight), and a nudge that Eddy's gear is a gamble. Pure dialogue, no outcomes.

### Chief Engineer Vex (vex_hail)
---
Speaker: chief_vex
When: comms
---
% Vex here. She's holding together. Mostly. What do you need?
% Engineering. Talk fast - I've got a coolant line arguing with me.
% If you're about to ask me to push the coils past redline again - no. Ask anyway.

- [How's the ship holding up?](vex_status)
- [What do you make of XORN?](vex_xorn)
- [Carry on, Chief](vex_bye)

### Chief Engineer Vex (vex_status)
---
Speaker: chief_vex
---
% She's a Warpster, not a warship. We win by being somewhere else when the shooting starts.
% Keep buying Eddy's junk and I'll keep bolting it on - just don't blame me when it bites.
% Give me a real salvage yard and a week and I'd make her sing. Failing that, we improvise.

- [Understood](vex_hail)

### Chief Engineer Vex (vex_xorn)
---
Speaker: chief_vex
---
% XORN outguns us at every turn. Our edge is the jump drive and knowing when to burn it.
% If that thing gets a firing solution we don't trade shots, we run. That's not cowardice, that's math.

- [Agreed](vex_hail)

### Chief Engineer Vex (vex_bye)
---
Speaker: chief_vex
---
% I'll be in the engine room. Where else would I be.

// Madame Skarr - the Skaraan rival who wants to SELL the Beacon (a foil to Storm, who wants
// its history, and XORN, which fears what it says). She hired the bounty hunters; hailing her
// lets you BRIBE them off (`costs 300 credits, signal hunters_bribed` -> a MAST route sets the
// suppress flag). The bounty crew's own hail is where the apathetic Dobbs answers "Whatever."

### Madame Skarr (skarr_hail)
