## Narrative

// The Beacon is NOT one relic you find - it is FIVE pieces the giants scattered so no single
// heir could ever wield it. Four hide in ruins you scan (Voice, Lens, Cipher, Heart); the
// fifth - the Cradle that seats and resonates them - the giants' heirs looted and lost to the
// black market, and Crazy Eddy has it. Episodes nest under one arc via HEADING LEVELS (`###`
// arc, `####` steps -> nested quest keys `beacon_arc/<step>`). Storm hands out leads one at a
// time (the data-driven `_eps` walker in story.mast); the finale ASSEMBLES the pieces, and
// scanning ruins alone can't finish it - without the Cradle bought from Eddy the Beacon has
// nothing to seat. See EPISODE_TEMPLATE.md to add more pieces.

### The Beacon Hunt (beacon_arc)
---
Scope: shared
State: active
---
Prof. Storm's search for the Beacon - which turns out to be no single relic but five pieces
the giants scattered across their ruins. Hail her for each lead, gather the pieces, and carry
them to the origin to be made whole.

#### Contact Prof. Storm (briefing)
---
Scope: shared
State: active
When: signal storm_briefed
---
Hail Prof. Storm on the Ultra-Beam (no target selected) for your first lead on the Beacon.

#### Storm's First Lead (ep1_go)
---
Scope: shared
State: secret
When: reach 2, -1
Then: reveal beacon_arc/ep1_scan
---
Storm's first heading: an ancient Torgoth channel out at (2, -1), coreward past the old
marches. Engage the jump drive from your Quests tab and follow it in.

#### The Voice (ep1_scan)
---
Scope: shared
State: secret
When: scan 1 derelict
Pays: 150 credits
---
A Torgoth megastation from the age when the Torgoth were giants. Deep in its dead heart sits
the Beacon's VOICE - the transmitter core, first of the five pieces. Scan it to take the
Voice, then hail Storm.

#### Storm's Next Lead (ep2_go)
---
Scope: shared
State: secret
When: reach 4, 1
Then: reveal beacon_arc/ep2_scan
---
Storm cross-referenced the Voice against the old charts: the next piece lies in the Kralien
marches at (4, 1). Engage and jump.

#### The Lens (ep2_scan)
---
Scope: shared
State: secret
When: scan 1 derelict
Pays: 200 credits
---
A cold Kralien megastructure holding the Beacon's LENS - the focusing array that aims the
Voice. A Torgoth reclamation party wants it too. Scan it to take the Lens, then hail Storm.

#### Storm's Third Lead (ep3_go)
---
Scope: shared
State: secret
When: reach 6, -2
Then: reveal beacon_arc/ep3_scan
---
Two pieces in hand and Storm sees the shape of it now: the Beacon is an ARRAY, not a relic,
and it needs a CRADLE to seat the pieces - one the giants' heirs looted and lost. Of all
people, Crazy Eddy has it. Meanwhile the third piece, the Cipher, waits in a nebula-wrapped
relay at (6, -2). Engage and jump - and think about paying Eddy a visit.

#### The Cipher (ep3_scan)
---
Scope: shared
State: secret
When: scan 1 derelict
Pays: 200 credits
---
A relay drowned in bruise-violet nebula, holding the Beacon's CIPHER - the key that aligns
Voice and Lens into one signal. Scan it to take the Cipher, then hail Storm.

#### The Resonance Cradle (get_cradle)
---
Scope: shared
State: secret
When: signal beacon_cradle
---
The pieces are useless loose - they need the CRADLE to seat and resonate them, and Crazy Eddy
fenced the only one left. Hail Eddy on the Ultra-Beam (no target selected) and buy the
Resonance Cradle from his deals. Do it any time before the finale - the Beacon can't be lit
without it.

#### Storm's Fourth Lead (ep4_go)
---
Scope: shared
State: secret
When: reach -5, -4
Then: reveal beacon_arc/ep4_scan
---
The Cipher named the last ruin-piece and where it went: the HEART, the Beacon's power source -
and XORN hauled it out to a dead salvage yard at (-5, -4). You'll have to pry it loose from
under their guns. Engage, and be ready to run.

#### The Heart (ep4_scan)
---
Scope: shared
State: secret
When: scan 1 derelict
Pays: 300 credits
---
A gutted salvage yard at the edge of the dark, XORN's colors on the wrecks - this is where it
dragged the Beacon's HEART. Scan the Heart out from under their guns, then break for open
space and hail Storm. Do not linger here.

#### Storm's Last Lead (origin_go)
---
Scope: shared
State: secret
When: reach 0, -7
Then: reveal beacon_arc/origin_scan
---
Every ruin-piece in hand - Voice, Lens, Cipher, Heart - and (you did buy the Cradle?) the
frame to seat them. Storm has the origin at last: (0, -7), the deep dark past every chart,
where the giants first lit the Beacon. Carry the pieces home. Engage.

#### The Origin (origin_scan)
---
Scope: shared
State: secret
When: scan 1 derelict
---
The place the Beacon was born - a silent array adrift in the deepest dark, waiting a thousand
years for its pieces to come home. Scan it to bring the array online, then hail Storm to
assemble the Beacon. XORN will not let this happen quietly.

## Goals

// The win is gated, not automatic: scanning the origin only brings the array online. The
// actual victory fires on `signal beacon_lit`, which the Storm dispatcher (story.mast) emits
// ONLY when every piece is present - the four scanned ruins AND the Cradle bought from Eddy.
// Arrive without the Cradle and Storm sends you back to buy it. That gate is the puzzle.

### Light the Beacon (goal_light)
---
Scope: shared
State: active
When: signal beacon_lit
Win: true
Citation: At the origin, with XORN's guns lighting the dark, Prof. Storm seated the last piece in the Cradle and woke the Beacon. It did what the giants built it to do a thousand years ago - it called. And in its first clear note was their final warning: the thing that unmade the giants and drove them small and hidden, the thing XORN still answers to. The Beacon is whole, its message is logged, and one small ship flew home with a story the giants died to leave. XORN broke off into the dark. It will be back. So will you.
---
Gather all five pieces of the Beacon - the four ruin-pieces AND Eddy's Cradle - carry them to
the origin, and have Prof. Storm assemble and light it while XORN does everything to stop you.

## Regions

// Geography for the whole hunt: the old marches and the deep dark beyond, where the giants
// left their megastations to rot. A nebula-heavy frontier - moody skybox, faint violet map
// wash, few ports. One big Chebyshev square covering every ruin cell out to the origin.

### The Old Marches (old_marches)
---
Center: 0, -1
Radius: 8
Skybox: sky-neb2-rvb
Music: Artemis2
Color: #86c
Nebula mix: 55%
Station mix: 5%
Enemy mix: 10%
---
The frontier past the last charted buoy - the old marches, where the giants of an earlier age
left their megastations to rot in the drifting cloud, and where the trail runs out into the
deepest dark. Nebulae everywhere, few ports, and something always a jump behind you.

## Landmarks

### Torgoth Megastation (giants_house)
---
At: 2, -1
Kind: derelict
Terrain: nebula violet
Guards: skaraan 2
---
A derelict from the age of giants - a Torgoth station built to a scale no modern hull needs,
running dark for a thousand years, holding the Beacon's Voice in its dead heart. Scavengers
picked the trail up first - a light bounty-hunter wing loiters in the wreck's shadow.

### Kralien Ruin (kralien_ruin)
---
At: 4, 1
Kind: derelict
Terrain: asteroids
Guards: torgoth 3
---
A Kralien megastructure from their own age of giants, adrift and cold, holding the Beacon's
Lens. A Torgoth reclamation party gutted the outer decks and lingers - they want it too.

### The Cipher Relay (cipher_relay)
---
At: 6, -2
Kind: derelict
Terrain: nebula violet
Guards: skaraan 4
---
A lone relay drowned in bruise-violet nebula, older than the ruins that pointed here, holding
the Beacon's Cipher. Whatever else hunts the trail got here first: a hard escort loiters in
the murk.

### XORN Salvage Yard (heart_yard)
---
At: -5, -4
Kind: derelict
Terrain: asteroids
Guards: skaraan 5
---
Not a ruin - a kill-yard. XORN dragged the Beacon's Heart here and left a heavy screen on it,
wrecks and mines and a wing that answers to no flag but its own. Scan the Heart and run; this
is the last place to be caught still.

### The Origin Array (origin_array)
---
At: 0, -7
Kind: derelict
Terrain: nebula red
Guards: skaraan 4
---
The deepest dark past every chart - a vast silent array adrift where the giants first lit the
Beacon a thousand years ago, wrapped in a bruise-red shroud. It has waited this long. XORN
will arrive fast to see it never sings again.
